Package com.telenav.kivakit.core.value.count

Class Range<Value extends Numeric<Value>>

java.lang.Object
com.telenav.kivakit.core.value.count.Range<Value>
Type Parameters:
Value - A value that is Numeric, which includes Minimizable, Maximizable, Comparable, and NextIterator.
All Implemented Interfaces:
Countable, Contains<Value>, Mapper<Long,Value>, Zeroable, Comparable<Countable>, Iterable<Value>
public class Range<Value extends Numeric<Value>> extends Object implements Contains<Value>, Comparable<Countable>, Countable, Iterable<Value>, Mapper<Long,Value>
Represents a range of value objects from a minimum to a maximum.

Creation and Properties

Ranges can be created in two ways, as rangeExclusive(Numeric, Numeric, Function) ranges which do not include their maximum value, and as rangeInclusive(Numeric, Numeric, Function) ranges which do.

  • rangeInclusive(Numeric, Numeric, Function)
  • rangeExclusive(Numeric, Numeric, Function)
  • upperBound()
  • isInclusive()
  • isExclusive()
  • minimum()
  • inclusiveMaximum()
  • exclusiveMaximum()

Looping

The values in a range can be processed in a loop with these methods.

  • loop(Runnable)

Operations

  • constrained(Value)
  • containsInclusive(Value)
  • randomValue(Random)
